  "medusa_train_gpu_h": 0.019483883380889893,
  "go_no_go": "NO-GO-LOCAL-REALIZE \u2014 the MEASURED free-run realized E[T]=1.65 (tree-central; single-candidate 1.52) sits FAR below the break-even E[T]=3.42 needed to beat 442 at the measured 0.530 ms tax -> 214 TPS local (-228 vs 442; crosses_500=False). Medusa's structural advantage over #532's EAGLE-3 is REAL and confirmed \u2014 the parallel draft is ~3x CHEAPER than the serial linear-MTP draft, dropping the step 12% \u2014 but the E[T] REALIZATION gap dominates: a cheap on-pod train (free-run greedy on 80 workload seqs, frozen backbone, tied head, early-stopped) realizes head-1 acc 0.33 and decays, landing ~1.9x UNDER the literature CEILING E[T]=3.22 \u2014 and that ceiling is itself only MARGINAL (< 3.42). Same capability-unbuilt-locally barrier #532 found for EAGLE-3 (head collapse): a beat-442 Medusa needs a proper large-corpus cluster train, and even then central E[T] does not clear 442. Quality-safe by construction (byte-exact M=8 verify => output==greedy; PPL 2.3767, self-det r1-r2=1.0, drafter-invariant). Reference-trajectory cross-check (biased low) corroborates: E[T]_sc 1.43.",
  "go_no_go_rationale": "MEASUREMENT-DRIVEN verdict (supersedes the analytic projection): NO-GO-LOCAL-REALIZE \u2014 the MEASURED free-run realized E[T]=1.65 (tree-central; single-candidate 1.52) sits FAR below the break-even E[T]=3.42 needed to beat 442 at the measured 0.530 ms tax -> 214 TPS local (-228 vs 442; crosses_500=False). Medusa's structural advantage over #532's EAGLE-3 is REAL and confirmed \u2014 the parallel draft is ~3x CHEAPER than the serial linear-MTP draft, dropping the step 12% \u2014 but the E[T] REALIZATION gap dominates: a cheap on-pod train (free-run greedy on 80 workload seqs, frozen backbone, tied head, early-stopped) realizes head-1 acc 0.33 and decays, landing ~1.9x UNDER the literature CEILING E[T]=3.22 \u2014 and that ceiling is itself only MARGINAL (< 3.42). Same capability-unbuilt-locally barrier #532 found for EAGLE-3 (head collapse): a beat-442 Medusa needs a proper large-corpus cluster train, and even then central E[T] does not clear 442. Quality-safe by construction (byte-exact M=8 verify => output==greedy; PPL 2.3767, self-det r1-r2=1.0, drafter-invariant). Reference-trajectory cross-check (biased low) corroborates: E[T]_sc 1.43. || ANALYTIC-CEILING context: Medusa REVERSES the #532 EAGLE-3 tradeoff but lands MARGINAL, not a clean win. Mechanism: the parallel head draft is ~3x CHEAPER than the deployed serial linear-MTP drafter (measured tax 0.530 ms vs draft_gpu 1.554 ms), so the step drops 12% (8.75->7.73 ms) \u2014 the OPPOSITE sign of EAGLE-3's step INFLATION. BUT independent heads decay with depth (vs the MTP chain's conditioned increase), so E[T] drops 16% (MTP 3.85 -> Medusa central 3.22), and the cheaper step does NOT quite over-compensate at central: 416 TPS local (-26 vs 442). The verdict is a knife-edge E[T] race: at the measured 0.530 ms tax, Medusa beats 442 iff realized E[T] >= 3.42 and crosses 500 iff E[T] >= 3.87. The literature-anchored band is central 3.22 (just UNDER 442) / optimistic 3.62 (clears 442, approaches 500). So realized E[T] is THE deciding uncertainty \u2014 a cheap local Medusa-1 train (frozen backbone, tied 12288 lm_head, train only ResBlocks; plausibly IN-SLOT, unlike EAGLE-3's ~107 GPU-h cluster) would resolve it. Quality-safe by construction (byte-exact verify => output==greedy; PPL 2.3767, r1-r2=1.0 inherited from #523, drafter-invariant). HAPPY ACCIDENT: the base's existing 12288 lm_head-prune voids Medusa's usual reduced-vocab penalty (target restricted to the same keepset the head drafts over) AND gives the cheapest tax (int4-tied reuse).",
